TITLE: Configuring Notification Channel for Custom Sounds
DESCRIPTION: Prepares a notification channel on Android to use a custom sound for notifications. The sound file must be placed in the raw resource directory. The channel and its sound settings need to be defined and used when scheduling notifications on Android 8.0+.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v53.0.0/sdk/notifications.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Prepare the notification channel
await Notifications.setNotificationChannelAsync('new_emails', {
  name: 'E-mail notifications',
  importance: Notifications.AndroidImportance.HIGH,
  sound: 'email_sound.wav',
});

// Eg. schedule the notification
await Notifications.scheduleNotificationAsync({
  content: {
    title: "You've got mail! ðŸ“¬",
    body: 'Open the notification to read them all',
    sound: 'email_sound.wav',
  },
  trigger: {
    type: Notifications.SchedulableTriggerInputTypes.TIME_INTERVAL,
    seconds: 2,
    channelId: 'new_emails',
});
