TITLE: Listening to Barometer Sensor Data with Expo-Sensors in React Native (JSX)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet illustrates how to set up a barometer sensor listener using expo-sensors' Barometer module within a React Native functional component. It manages subscription state, subscribes and unsubscribes to data events, and displays live pressure and relative altitude data (altitude only on iOS). Required dependencies include expo-sensors and react-native. Inputs involve user actions (toggling the listener); outputs are UI updates displaying air pressure and altitude measurements. Limitations: relative altitude is only available on iOS, and web is not supported.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v50.0.0/sdk/barometer.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

