TITLE: Looping Media a Specific Number of Times in JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript example demonstrating how to make a media item loop exactly N times (20 in this case). It uses the `_onPlaybackStatusUpdate` callback to track the number of times the media has finished playing (`didJustFinish`). When the desired number of loops is reached, `setIsLooping(false)` is called to stop further looping. Initially, looping is enabled via `playbackObject.setIsLooping(true)`.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v50.0.0/sdk/av.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
```js
const N = 20;
/* @hide ... */ /* @end */

_onPlaybackStatusUpdate = playbackStatus => {
  if (playbackStatus.didJustFinish) {
    if (this.state.numberOfLoops == N - 1) {
      playbackObject.setIsLooping(false);
    }
    this.setState({ numberOfLoops: this.state.numberOfLoops + 1 });
  }
};

/* @hide ... */ /* @end */
this.setState({ numberOfLoops: 0 });
// Load the playbackObject and obtain the reference.
playbackObject.setOnPlaybackStatusUpdate(this._onPlaybackStatusUpdate);
playbackObject.setIsLooping(true);
```
```

