TITLE: Creating a Custom Keyboard Height Hook in React Native with TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: This snippet defines a custom hook called useGradualAnimation that uses the useKeyboardHandler hook to track keyboard height changes. It returns a shared value that can be used for animations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/guides/keyboard-handling.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
import { useKeyboardHandler } from 'react-native-keyboard-controller';
import Animated, { useAnimatedStyle, useSharedValue } from 'react-native-reanimated';

const useGradualAnimation = () => {
  const height = useSharedValue(0);

  useKeyboardHandler(
    {
      onMove: event => {
        'worklet';
        height.value = Math.max(event.height, 0);
      },
    },
    []
  );
  return { height };
};
```

