TITLE: Configuring Babel with Webpack for Next.js
DESCRIPTION: Conditional Babel configuration that adds next/babel preset when bundling with webpack for web.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/guides/using-nextjs.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
module.exports = function (api) {
  const isWeb = api.caller(
    caller =>
      caller && (caller.name === 'babel-loader' || caller.name === 'next-babel-turbo-loader')
  );
  return {
    presets: [
      isWeb && require('next/babel'),
      'babel-preset-expo',
    ].filter(Boolean),
  };
};
```

