TITLE: Defining Manifest and Asset Types in Expo Update Protocol (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: Defines the Manifest and Asset types used in Expo's update protocol. These types ensure that JSON bodies in update responses conform to expected structures, with fields for IDs, versioning, assets, and metadata. Dependencies include TypeScript and a JSON serialization mechanism; inputs and outputs are JSON objects matching the defined structures. Asset objects provide content type, hash, and location information, while Manifest aggregates update-level metadata; clients validate fields such as hash and content-type against protocol requirements.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/technical-specs/expo-updates-1.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
type Manifest = {
  id: string;
  createdAt: string;
  runtimeVersion: string;
  launchAsset: Asset;
  assets: Asset[];
  metadata: { [key: string]: string };
  extra: { [key: string]: any };
};

type Asset = {
  hash?: string;
  key: string;
  contentType: string;
  fileExtension?: string;
  url: string;
};
```

