TITLE: Moving and Copying Files with expo-file-system/next in TypeScript
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a text file and then move it between different locations in the file system. Shows how file URIs are updated after moving operations.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v53.0.0/sdk/filesystem-next.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: TypeScript
CODE:
```
import { File, Paths } from 'expo-file-system/next';

try {
  const file = new File(Paths.document, 'example.txt');
  file.create();
  console.log(file.uri); // '${documentDirectory}/example.txt'
  file.move(Paths.cache);
  console.log(file.uri); // '${cacheDirectory}/example.txt'
  file.move(new Directory(Paths.cache, 'newFolder'));
  console.log(file.uri); // '${cacheDirectory}/newFolder/example.txt'
} catch (error) {
  console.error(error);
}
```

