TITLE: Implementing Convertible Protocol in Swift for CMTime
DESCRIPTION: Example implementation of the Convertible protocol for CMTime type, demonstrating how to convert JavaScript values to native Swift types. The convert method handles conversion of Double values to CMTime instances with maximum precision.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/modules/module-api.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_24

LANGUAGE: swift
CODE:
```
import ExpoModulesCore

extension CMTime: @retroactive Convertible {
  public static func convert(from value: Any?, appContext: AppContext) throws -> CMTime {
    if let seconds = value as? Double {
      return CMTime(seconds: seconds, preferredTimescale: .max)
    }
    throw Conversions.ConvertingException<CMTime>(value)
  }
}
```

