TITLE: Implementing Media Looping with Counter
DESCRIPTION: JavaScript code showing how to implement precise control over media looping by counting loop iterations. This example demonstrates how to loop media exactly 20 times before stopping playback.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v51.0.0/sdk/av.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const N = 20;

_onPlaybackStatusUpdate = playbackStatus => {
  if (playbackStatus.didJustFinish) {
    if (this.state.numberOfLoops == N - 1) {
      playbackObject.setIsLooping(false);
    }
    this.setState({ numberOfLoops: this.state.numberOfLoops + 1 });
  }
};

this.setState({ numberOfLoops: 0 });
// Load the playbackObject and obtain the reference.
playbackObject.setOnPlaybackStatusUpdate(this._onPlaybackStatusUpdate);
playbackObject.setIsLooping(true);
```

