TITLE: Schema-Only Validation - JavaScript
DESCRIPTION: This JavaScript snippet demonstrates how to perform schema-only validation using the Schemer library. A JSON schema is imported into the validator, which is then used to asynchronously validate data against the schema. Errors are caught and logged if validation fails. This requires schema.json and data.json files for schema and data definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/packages/@expo/schemer/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
const validator = new Schemer(require('schema.json'));
try {
  await validator.validateSchemaAsync(require('data.json'));
} catch (e) {
  console.error(e);
}
```

