TITLE: BlurHash Generation Endpoint Implementation
DESCRIPTION: Express.js endpoint that processes uploaded images and generates BlurHash values with configurable component parameters.
SOURCE: https://github.com/expo/expo/blob/main/docs/pages/versions/v50.0.0/sdk/image.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
app.post('/blurhash', upload.single('image'), async (req, res) => {
  const { file } = req;
  if (file === null) {
    res.status(400).json({ message: 'Image is missing' });
    return;
  }

  const componentX = req.body.componentX ?? 4;
  const componentY = req.body.componentY ?? 3;

  const { data, info } = await sharp(file.buffer).ensureAlpha().raw().toBuffer({
    resolveWithObject: true,
  });

  const blurhash = encode(
    new Uint8ClampedArray(data),
    info.width,
    info.height,
    componentX,
    componentY
  );
  res.json({ blurhash });
});
```

